flowRoot.flowPara: "Auto" is a toggle button - pressing it moves the sliders to an automatically determined position. The sliders can still be moved independently - manually changing them pushes the auto button back out (but does not reset).

text.tspan: - "magic" mode by default, detailed controls secondary

flowRoot.flowPara: Buttons allow 90° rotations and vertical flip.
Overlaid grid is shown while rotate is selected.
Dragging on the canvas allows fine tuning rotation (+/- 7.5° only). When fine tune is active, a cancel button is shown next to the current value.
When fine-tuning, dragging should "stick" to the original 0.0 position.
Preview button toggles between original image and cropped image. It should be insensitive when no changes have been made to the crop.

Cropping is specific in that it needs to be applied and yet allow re-editing. I suggest to expand and collapse every tool by clicking its header. All other tools expose editing with sliders on the side, but perhaps we'll allow onscreen position for some filters (spot removal).
